<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-3084] Groovy scripts can&apos;t access the &apos;args&apos; property anymore to get the arguments from the command line</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3084</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;macpro:~ sam$ cat /tmp/test.groovy &lt;br/&gt;
println args&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;macpro:~ sam$ ~/Software/groovy-1.6-beta-2/bin/groovy /tmp/test.groovy&lt;br/&gt;
Caught: groovy.lang.MissingPropertyException: No such property: args for class: test&lt;br/&gt;
	at test.run(test.groovy:1)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The exact same thing will work on any previous version of groovy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Mac OS X 10.5, Java 1.6</environment>
